about style in my crowd.

06:00.200 --> 06:04.360
Sure. It looks all right.

06:22.920 --> 06:25.600
[door closes]

06:25.680 --> 06:28.360
- Hello there!
- [chuckles]

06:28.440 --> 06:31.400
Have to admit I was a little
puzzled to hear you were coming.

06:31.480 --> 06:33.080
[in English]
What's the matter?

06:33.160 --> 06:35.720
A guy can't come say hello
to a pal away at college?

06:35.800 --> 06:37.760
[chuckles]

06:37.840 --> 06:41.840
Somehow I doubt this is a social call.
What's up?

06:41.920 --> 06:43.200
I need a favor.

06:45.560 --> 06:47.440
[in Norwegian] Do you remember
how I ended up in here?

06:47.520 --> 06:51.160
Kind of far out for you to show up here
and ask me for a favor.

06:53.080 --> 06:56.560
[in English] What I would recommend
for the remainder of this conversation...

06:58.040 --> 07:01.240
...is a little less focus on the past

07:01.320 --> 07:03.720
and little more on the future.

07:03.800 --> 07:05.760
My friend here,

07:05.840 --> 07:08.640
he's got people in high places.

07:08.720 --> 07:11.160
Get you out of here in a couple of days.

07:16.080 --> 07:18.840
Okay. What can I do for you?

07:21.520 --> 07:24.040
You heard about this Bieber Heist?

07:24.120 --> 07:25.720
Yeah.

07:25.800 --> 07:27.720
Amongst other things,

07:27.800 --> 07:30.480
these individuals purloined

07:30.560 --> 07:34.320
certain objects of value
to me and my friend here.

07:34.400 --> 07:36.520
Well, we would endeavor to have
a conversation

07:36.600 --> 07:39.800
with these same individuals,
if at all possible.

07:39.880 --> 07:44.000
Well, I don't know
who the robbers are...

07:44.080 --> 07:47.120
[in Norwegian] ...but I know someone
who might be able to help.

07:47.200 --> 07:50.720
You heard about "The Orange"?

07:50.800 --> 07:54.160
He's like the banker for robbers.

07:54.240 --> 07:55.400
[in English]
Orange?

07:57.320 --> 07:58.800
Is he from Miami?

07:58.880 --> 08:01.440
[chuckles]

08:01.520 --> 08:03.760
[in English]
No. Not quite.

08:03.840 --> 08:07.640
[in Norwegian] He takes B12 injections
to get a tan. Fucking vain guy.

08:08.560 --> 08:12.360
[in English]
Okay. How do we find this fruit?

08:12.440 --> 08:16.800
[in Norwegian] I'll let you know as soon
as my new date of release is confirmed.

08:21.600 --> 08:22.720
[in English]
Okay?

08:26.320 --> 08:28.600
[Torgeir in Norwegian] You're supposed
to pay the staff price for that beer.

08:28.680 --> 08:30.080
Oh, relax.

08:30.160 --> 08:31.760
You'll have to accept a little shrinkage.

08:31.840 --> 08:33.120
Are you leaving?

08:33.200 --> 08:35.320
Yeah, I have to stop by the asylum center.

08:35.400 --> 08:37.240
