That's Mom's boyfriend.

42:08.920 --> 42:10.800
Hope I'm not interrupting.

42:10.880 --> 42:13.240
[in English] I got a business opportunity
I want to pitch to you.

42:13.320 --> 42:14.680
[in Norwegian]
You're interrupting big-time.

42:14.760 --> 42:18.040
We are having
an executive meeting here, so...

42:18.120 --> 42:20.160
[in English]
Stanley's just about to leave.

42:20.240 --> 42:22.920
Now, now, let's not be hasty,
Mr. Managing Director.

42:23.000 --> 42:26.000
After all, he's practically
part of the family.

42:26.080 --> 42:27.720
Let's hear what he has to say.

42:29.640 --> 42:33.520
[in Norwegian] Before I became religious,
I played some music.

42:36.320 --> 42:38.520
Hi, guys.

42:38.600 --> 42:40.320
This is my old band.

42:40.400 --> 42:42.280
[Johhny in English]
How are you doing?

42:42.360 --> 42:46.120
[in Norwegian] We're gonna fit perfectly
with Flamingo's profile.

42:51.520 --> 42:53.840
[in English]
Oh! This is beautiful.

42:53.920 --> 42:55.920
This is music to my eyes.

42:56.000 --> 42:57.280
- I love this.
- [Stanley] Yeah.

42:57.360 --> 42:59.160
I listened when you talk to the boys

42:59.240 --> 43:02.440
and I knew you got some liquor problem.

43:02.520 --> 43:04.320
Huh.

43:04.400 --> 43:07.160
I'm afraid to ask.
What's the deal?

43:07.240 --> 43:09.320
Well, I checked the numbers with Roar.

43:09.400 --> 43:11.400
We are cheaper than the last guy.

43:13.520 --> 43:15.560
[chuckles]

43:15.640 --> 43:17.240
You know,

43:17.320 --> 43:20.040
I've been in a bit
of a dark tunnel lately.

43:20.120 --> 43:23.360
You showed me a little light.
Thank you.

43:23.440 --> 43:25.360
The kids could use
a father figure like you.

43:25.440 --> 43:27.280
[Johnny and Stanley chuckle]

43:27.360 --> 43:29.280
- [Stanley] Yeah.
- [Johnny] Let's have a drink.

43:29.360 --> 43:30.920
[Stanley]
Okay.

43:31.000 --> 43:33.440
[Moby Grapes' "Can't Be So Bad" playing]
